rnocleidomastoid is that big neck muscle.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048563,0.093424,0.10001,0.10355,0.10031,0.098708,0.093577,0.085832,0.087909,0.072807,0.061467,0.053839],"unified_progress":[0.053944,0.08044,0.097437,0.10802,0.11104,0.10583,0.099595,0.089964,0.08723,0.068596,0.053819,0.044088]},{"section":10,"text":"The upper part...","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.34072,0.056511,0.057056,0.06479,0.063177,0.06307,0.058931,0.065148,0.064808,0.058607,0.061221,0.04596],"unified_progress":[0.23307,0.089763,0.071058,0.069249,0.078,0.073466,0.08462,0.076674,0.070734,0.055583,0.050189,0.047589]},{"section":11,"text":"so maybe a lymph node swelling?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047573,0.10069,0.072986,0.11691,0.11158,0.10125,0.096163,0.087866,0.079182,0.071632,0.06303,0.051138],"unified_progress":[0.053095,0.093334,0.081801,0.1138,0.11766,0.1076,0.098309,0.090432,0.07772,0.068564,0.056837,0.040843]},{"section":12,"text":"Or an abscess spreading there?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036763,0.082007,0.096299,0.10378,0.10349,0.10104,0.096865,0.089389,0.091534,0.077939,0.065907,0.054985],"unified_progress":[0.039358,0.078054,0.097305,0.11213,0.11355,0.10477,0.10183,0.091762,0.088097,0.072131,0.056778,0.044237]},{"section":13,"text":"Wait, after a tooth extraction, dental infections can spread.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040837,0.082266,0.093785,0.099104,0.09957,0.10002,0.095409,0.090358,0.087681,0.082899,0.06925,0.058824],"unified_progress":[0.065611,0.093597,0.096479,0.10103,0.10047,0.095328,0.093057,0.088605,0.082947,0.073885,0.06051,0.048481]},{"section":14,"text":"The classic ones are things like Ludwig's angina, but that's usually more in the floor of the mouth, causing swelling there and maybe airway obstruction.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034008,0.072699,0.085618,0.094967,0.099761,0.1015,0.1018,0.09622,0.092375,0.086044,0.07366,0.061342],"unified_progress":[0.040404,0.06847,0.088745,0.096157,0.10154,0.10738,0.1011,0.097111,0.09315,0.085258,0.068911,0.05177]},{"section":15,"text":"But this patient has trismus, which is more associated with infections involving the muscles of mastication, like maybe a parapharyngeal abscess or a submandibular space infection?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036427,0.078851,0.090099,0.097132,0.098211,0.099868,0.098334,0.092183,0.095045,0.081751,0.070571,0.061527],"unified_progress":[0.040269,0.071889,0.089987,0.10165,0.106,0.10523,0.1009,0.094912,0.094103,0.078826,0.064922,0.051306]},{"section":16,"text":"The parapharyngeal space is near the tonsils.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034993,0.079444,0.092932,0.10085,0.10017,0.10091,0.097952,0.090295,0.096108,0.079062,0.068036,0.059246],"unified_progress":[0.040645,0.074003,0.094702,0.10825,0.11222,0.10694,0.10238,0.092783,0.091659,0.072744,0.057046,0.046624]},{"section":17,"text":"If there's an abscess there, it could push the tonsils medially.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035672,0.081974,0.095135,0.10314,0.10103,0.10132,0.097504,0.088938,0.095287,0.077302,0.065535,0.057166],"unified_progress":[0.039604,0.074865,0.096703,0.11124,0.11535,0.10708,0.10318,0.092366,0.09083,0.069531,0.054102,0.045154]},{"section":18,"text":"Also, trismus can occur because the infection might involve the muscles around the jaw, making it hard to open the mouth.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035823,0.073968,0.084112,0.092555,0.097481,0.10055,0.10153,0.096384,0.094376,0.084153,0.075804,0.063261],"unified_progress":[0.07036,0.069646,0.080881,0.089266,0.09664,0.096395,0.09666,0.094281,0.09148,0.082305,0.072366,0.059719]},{"section":19,"text":"The swelling in the neck at the sternocleidomastoid area... maybe the infection has spread down along the neck?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034956,0.081095,0.093968,0.1009,0.098749,0.10053,0.09717,0.089408,0.097045,0.078113,0.068138,0.059926],"unified_progress":[0.038465,0.076668,0.098818,0.10899,0.11316,0.10595,0.10115,0.090482,0.090043,0.071596,0.056796,0.047884]},{"section":20,"text":"Or perhaps it's a lymph node reaction, but more likely an abscess tracking down?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031922,0.072167,0.086163,0.095111,0.098246,0.10007,0.099634,0.095462,0.097652,0.086061,0.075252,0.062263],"unified_progress":[0.038759,0.072063,0.091317,0.10336,0.1079,0.10192,0.10268,0.095159,0.092025,0.079156,0.064394,0.051266]},{"section":21,"text":"Another thought: the sternocleidomastoid is part of the anterior triangle of the neck.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039807,0.079857,0.089383,0.096301,0.097054,0.098698,0.096407,0.091044,0.094414,0.081295,0.071738,0.064001],"unified_progress":[0.04963,0.075105,0.09218,0.1035,0.10746,0.10343,0.099739,0.092344,0.089511,0.074693,0.061589,0.050817]},{"section":22,"text":"The upper part might be related to the submandibular or submental spaces, but if it's higher up, maybe the infection is in the parapharyngeal space and has extended into the neck.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034011,0.079865,0.094067,0.10236,0.10056,0.10114,0.097827,0.089485,0.097912,0.077874,0.066959,0.057937],"unified_progress":[0.041135,0.076375,0.09832,0.11217,0.11544,0.10657,0.10237,0.091439,0.090125,0.068598,0.053297,0.044165]},{"section":23,"text":"Wait, the parapharyngeal space infections can indeed cause medial displacement of the tonsils.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034907,0.0751,0.087842,0.096909,0.099219,0.10071,0.098945,0.092728,0.095366,0.082141,0.072833,0.0633],"unified_progress":[0.045657,0.072351,0.091696,0.10437,0.1088,0.10606,0.10166,0.093141,0.089969,0.075299,0.060724,0.050263]},{"section":24,"text":"The trismus is due to involvement of the medial pterygoid muscle, which is part of the mastication muscles.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03486,0.074747,0.086582,0.095393,0.098745,0.10088,0.10023,0.094118,0.094172,0.082929,0.073229,0.064112],"unified_progress":[0.05609,0.071744,0.088596,0.10005,0.10394,0.10446,0.099342,0.092837,0.089188,0.07631,0.06375,0.053687]},{"section":25,"text":"The swelling in the neck could be an abscess extending into the neck, maybe into the carotid sheath area?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033038,0.078934,0.09313,0.10138,0.099898,0.10139,0.098332,0.090158,0.097828,0.078495,0.068074,0.059341],"unified_progress":[0.036505,0.075238,0.098284,0.11115,0.11534,0.10669,0.10255,0.091776,0.090873,0.070026,0.055394,0.046173]},{"section":26,"text":"The sternocleidomastoid is near the carotid sheath, so maybe the infection is spreading there.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038407,0.081241,0.092479,0.10046,0.099513,0.10036,0.0968,0.089398,0.094964,0.078474,0.067583,0.060327],"unified_progress":[0.046947,0.076166,0.095727,0.10853,0.11296,0.10443,0.10155,0.091416,0.088991,0.070232,0.055767,0.047287]},{"section":27,"text":"Alternatively, could it be a peritonsillar abscess?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031106,0.068305,0.082602,0.09264,0.099124,0.1012,0.10153,0.098787,0.098407,0.088256,0.077436,0.060607],"unified_progress":[0.039425,0.072848,0.093688,0.10641,0.1083,0.10533,0.10447,0.095349,0.089624,0.077584,0.061122,0.045846]},{"section":28,"text":"But peritonsillar would push the tonsil to one side, but maybe not medially.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034981,0.072539,0.083382,0.092213,0.096759,0.099716,0.10071,0.096877,0.095889,0.086606,0.076629,0.063698],"unified_progress":[0.044475,0.070759,0.088757,0.099346,0.10529,0.10529,0.10136,0.096803,0.091969,0.081223,0.065384,0.049341]},{"section":29,"text":"Also, peritonsillar abscess is more common in younger adults, but the history of tooth extraction might point more towards a dental source.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029518,0.064062,0.077176,0.086981,0.094354,0.10078,0.10235,0.10133,0.098195,0.094975,0.083995,0.066278],"unified_progress":[0.053253,0.082002,0.086515,0.089613,0.094399,0.096853,0.095187,0.096891,0.091801,0.088867,0.072128,0.052492]},{"section":30,"text":"Wait, parapharyngeal abscess often comes from dental infections, like from the molars.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028883,0.065689,0.080204,0.090708,0.096664,0.10122,0.10141,0.097194,0.10112,0.08949,0.079065,0.068359],"unified_progress":[0.047381,0.076876,0.091185,0.098858,0.10086,0.10202,0.097864,0.09362,0.092828,0.079071,0.066341,0.053095]},{"section":31,"text":"Since he had a tooth extraction, maybe that's the source.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035678,0.072137,0.081623,0.088958,0.09539,0.10501,0.099256,0.097783,0.094701,0.090372,0.077341,0.061748],"unified_progress":[0.097012,0.12324,0.10303,0.094428,0.089465,0.086684,0.080912,0.083411,0.074602,0.065502,0.056092,0.045624]},{"section":32,"text":"The spread of infection from the tooth to the parapharyngeal space.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030564,0.069218,0.082764,0.092046,0.095472,0.098458,0.099574,0.093384,0.10801,0.084721,0.07704,0.068751],"unified_progress":[0.067734,0.080636,0.092579,0.098448,0.10143,0.095834,0.092377,0.087304,0.092261,0.072831,0.063329,0.055235]},{"section":33,"text":"The medial displacement of the tonsil is a key sign here.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0313,0.068811,0.082046,0.090557,0.094007,0.096684,0.097908,0.094415,0.098183,0.089457,0.082795,0.073837],"unified_progress":[0.054865,0.071356,0.086501,0.095455,0.10073,0.098213,0.09667,0.09228,0.090962,0.081625,0.070894,0.060449]},{"section":34,"text":"Trismus is also a sign because the parapharyngeal space is near the muscles involved in jaw movement.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029454,0.066028,0.079512,0.089826,0.09588,0.0998,0.10224,0.09816,0.09885,0.088956,0.082,0.069291],"unified_progress":[0.079616,0.069493,0.082099,0.090737,0.096587,0.096679,0.095043,0.092157,0.08913,0.080263,0.069723,0.058476]},{"section":35,"text":"The neck swelling at the upper sternocleidomastoid could be the abscess extending inferiorly along the neck, maybe into the carotid sheath or the submandibular area.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033147,0.077005,0.089962,0.09804,0.097431,0.10023,0.098009,0.091116,0.09814,0.081125,0.071549,0.064246],"unified_progress":[0.039006,0.075219,0.098587,0.10816,0.11258,0.10516,0.10099,0.090761,0.089242,0.071608,0.058249,0.050445]},{"section":36,"text":"Another possibility is Ludwig's angina, but that's more in the floor of the mouth, leading to swelling under the tongue and difficulty swallowing, but trismus might not be as prominent.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02811,0.062887,0.075996,0.086751,0.09459,0.099432,0.10376,0.10208,0.099565,0.094203,0.084889,0.067732],"unified_progress":[0.035977,0.063436,0.080518,0.090765,0.09904,0.10468,0.10191,0.10137,0.097445,0.093215,0.075834,0.055815]},{"section":37,"text":"Plus, the tonsils being pushed medially isn't typical for Ludwig's.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023902,0.056059,0.070868,0.081406,0.089344,0.095577,0.10331,0.10535,0.10561,0.10142,0.094605,0.072543],"unified_progress":[0.031366,0.05821,0.074255,0.083927,0.094378,0.097354,0.10101,0.10495,0.10394,0.10618,0.086307,0.058121]},{"section":38,"text":"So putting it all together: dental extraction leading to parapharyngeal abscess.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031534,0.060878,0.070738,0.078372,0.083467,0.087829,0.091203,0.092132,0.097115,0.095379,0.095575,0.11578],"unified_progress":[0.04106,0.053137,0.063445,0.073667,0.078592,0.084684,0.087766,0.09086,0.095403,0.095215,0.10837,0.1278]},{"section":39,"text":"Symptoms include fever, trismus, medial displacement of tonsils, and a neck swelling.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027665,0.057662,0.066103,0.073514,0.082312,0.090349,0.095983,0.098714,0.10336,0.10243,0.10557,0.096331],"unified_progress":[0.038457,0.055615,0.064863,0.072364,0.082135,0.091335,0.093893,0.099464,0.10463,0.10626,0.10381,0.087173]},{"section":40,"text":"The most likely diagnosis is parapharyngeal abscess.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020022,0.044756,0.055702,0.064024,0.071739,0.079246,0.086638,0.090998,0.1011,0.10247,0.1157,0.16761],"unified_progress":[0.019961,0.036176,0.046648,0.056064,0.062458,0.076129,0.07991,0.092944,0.10459,0.10878,0.13867,0.17767]},{"section":41,"text":"<answer> Parapharyngeal abscess </answer>","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027892,0.049965,0.053958,0.059688,0.067419,0.075816,0.083574,0.090078,0.099492,0.10345,0.11597,0.1727],"unified_progress":[0.027702,0.035209,0.041558,0.049221,0.055258,0.066081,0.070668,0.086188,0.098235,0.10904,0.14837,0.21247]}]}}